
[1]rehearsal

   REHEARSAL, n. rehers'al. [from rehearse.]

   1. Recital; repetition of the words of another or of a written work; as
   the rehearsal of the Lord's prayer.

   2. Narration; a telling or recounting, as of particulars in detail; as
   the rehearsal of a soldier's adventures.

   3. The recital of a place before the public exhibition of it; as the
   rehearsal of a comedy.
